<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Back to the topic, giving mages a slow type spell makes about as much sense as giving them the mez/charm spells. Which is no sense at all.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Here's what doesn't make sense.<br>
<br>
To hear absor or whoever state that its ok that we can't solo in the end game b/c we were so good at it at the beginning of the game.  What kind of logic is that?  I picked a mage b/c I liked tough pets and I really liked how they could solo pretty well.  But then after a couple expansions and a hell of a lot of game time, I'm to be told that my class all of a sudden should be weak solo'er in order to balance it out.  <br>
<br>
Balance is one thing, but a class should have a natural and progressive trend of keeping the same playing pattern while at the same time getting stronger and better at that playing pattern.  By taking away our ability to solo at the end game, they have destroyed that smooth progressive trend.<br>
<br>
I think giving mages slow is a great idea.  But it doesn't have to be slow.. they could also restore our trend of being good at soloing by upping our pets HP to a point where they can tank a mob for us while we nuke it down. Or give us a pet only CH spell at level 60 or 61.<br>
